    <thetext>I&apos;m running Fedora25 cloud image on AArch64 VM, which runs on AArch64 host. After upgrading to 4.9.13 kernel, networking breaks (NIC is down after boot). I find NIC mac address changes every time I reboot the VM.

Run &quot;ethtool -P eth0&quot; shows NIC permanent address is all zero, so a random address is selected.
$ sudo ethtool -P eth0
Permanent address: 00:00:00:00:00:00

Returning to old kernels (4.9.10, 4.8.6) resolves this problem.</thetext>
